{
  "text": "The force from an external magnetic-field, F M , can be derived from the formula [CITATION_1] , F M = J M \u00d7\u03c6 0\u1e91 , where J M is the screening-current, \u03c6 0 = 2.07\u00d710 \u221215 Wb is the flux quantum, and\u1e91 is the unit vector parallel to the z-axis. The calculation of J M is a two-dimensional problem that can be formulated on the complex plane of the complex variable \u03b6 = x + iy, which can be easily solved by using the conformal mapping that maps the SC with flat surface on the complex w-plane into that with groove on the \u03b6-plane (see Appendix A). Then the components of J M are given by [CITATION_2] ",
